\mathop {\lim }\limits_{x \to \pm \infty } {a \over x} = 0
\lim\limits_{x\to\pm\infty}\dfrac{a}{x}=0
\epsilon>0
M\ge 0
\left|\dfrac{a}{x}-0\right|<\epsilon
|x|>M
x\ne 0
\epsilon>0,
\left|\dfrac{a}{x}-0\right|<\epsilon
\dfrac{|a|}{\epsilon}<|x|.
\left|\frac{a}{x}-0\right|=\left|\frac{a}{x}\right|=\frac{|a|}{|x|},
